From 83d0261a5eafe14ffd4187c0c97a02d8798afca3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 05:36:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(taxonomy-graph): derive from real catalog data, write
 orphan fixes back to coreStore (Phase 4)

Root cause found while wiring this up: TaxonomyGraphView.tsx passed
activeUcid?.id as the graph hook's configId, but allConfigs holds
Config objects with unrelated cfg-* ids -- the internal id lookup
could never match for any real UCID. That's *why* the graph always
silently showed the same stale content regardless of selection: the
one successful fetch (using the DEFAULT_CONFIGS placeholder before a
UCID resolved) never got replaced, because every subsequent lookup
failed and returned early without touching state.

- useCatalogGraphData.ts: replaced the network round-trip + broken id
  lookup with deriveGraphFromConfig(), a pure function building nodes/
  edges directly from the selected config's real BOM items crossed
  against catalogSkus. No 600ms simulated delay either.
- mapNode/healOrphanMapping now write the classification onto the
  matching real catalog SKU via setCatalogSkus (by partNumber), or
  create a new SKU if none exists yet. The next catalogSkus-triggered
  re-derivation shows the fix automatically -- and because it's a
  real coreStore write, the fix is now visible on Dashboard, Catalog
  Manager, and Cleansing too, not just the graph view.
- TaxonomyGraphSidebar.tsx: removed the now-redundant duplicate
  setCatalogSkus call in handleMapOrphanNode -- mapNode owns this
  write now, avoiding two slightly-different copies of the same logic.
- Generic node/edge CRUD (add/update/delete) now operates on a local
  GraphOverlay that layers on top of the derived baseline, so a
  manual edit survives a catalogSkus-triggered re-derivation instead
  of being silently wiped -- same non-destructive-merge principle
  used for CleansingView in Phase 2.
- Fixed an id-scheme bug caught mid-implementation: orphan node ids
  must be the real partNumber, since the pre-existing
  OrphanWorkshopPanel/handleMapOrphanNode code already assumes an
  orphan's id IS its partNumber.
- Retired memoryGraphNodes/memoryGraphEdges and the 5 dead MSW graph
  CRUD routes that served them, after confirming zero remaining
  callers. Left alternative-paths/path-selection alone (genuinely
  algorithmic, still network-backed on purpose).
- Rewrote taxonomy-graph-sync.test.tsx (6 tests: pure derivation,
  catalog write-back, live orphan resolution on catalogSkus change,
  no-duplicate-on-remap) and MSWContracts.test.ts's dead-route schema
  check (now validates deriveGraphFromConfig's output instead).

Noted, not fixed: TaxonomyOrphanBox.tsx (a second, fully unused
component with the 'Orphan Work Queue (1) renders empty' bug found
earlier) is dead code with zero imports -- left in place since file
deletion is higher-risk than route cleanup and it was never reachable
in the running app anyway.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, full vitest suite green (84 files /
397 tests, 0 regressions).
